# Theme & Styling

## Token layers

1. `app/theme.css` — `--palette-*` and semantic tokens (`--background-*`, `--text-*`, `--layout-*`)
2. `app/globals.css` — `@theme inline` maps tokens to Tailwind utilities (must live in the Tailwind entry file)

## In components

Use semantic Tailwind classes, never hardcoded hex:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<p className="text-[#6B7280]">Helper</p>

// ✅ GOOD
<p className="text-helper">Helper</p>
<h1 className="text-heading">Title</h1>
<button className="bg-btn-primary text-on-solid">Save</button>
```

## Key utilities

| Purpose | Class |
|---|---|
| Page background | `bg-body` |
| Body text | `text-foreground` |
| Headings | `text-heading` |
| Helper text | `text-helper` |
| Tabs | `text-tab`, `text-tab-active`, `text-disabled` |
| Buttons | `bg-btn-primary`, `bg-btn-accent` |
| Surfaces | `bg-subtle`, `bg-muted`, `bg-inverse` |
| Borders | `border-border` |
| Header height | `h-header` (56px via `--layout-header-height`) |
| Sidebar width | `w-sidebar` (224px via `--layout-sidebar-width`) |

## Changing colors

- Edit palette/semantic vars in `app/theme.css` only
- Use `@theme inline` (not plain `@theme`) to support future theme switching
- Base element styles belong in `app/globals.css`
